    <h1>STRANGER THINGS (2016 to present)</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200906/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-06"><time>2020-09-06</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE I FEATURES</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>In 2018, a for­mer crew mem­ber of the hit Net­flix hor­ror-sci­ence-fic­tion se­ries ac­cused cre­ators and twin broth­ers Matt and Ross Duf­fer (both above) of be­ing ver­bally abu­sive on set.</p>
    <p>Pey­ton Brown wrote on In­sta­gram: “I per­son­ally wit­nessed two men in high po­si­tions of power on that set seek out and ver­bally abuse mul­ti­ple women.”</p>
    <p>Net­flix con­ducted an in­ter­nal in­ves­ti­ga­tion, but found no wrong­do­ing.</p>
    <p>The broth­ers later apol­o­gised in a state­ment: “Due to the high-stress na­ture of pro­duc­tion, tem­pers oc­ca­sion­ally get frayed.”</p>
    <p>They added that they were com­mit­ted to pro­vid­ing a safe work­ing en­vi­ron­ment.</p>

